details.text: This read-only memory contains information for the host about the system and about each kernel in the system, including kernel names, arguments, and attributes. The system description ROM ensures that the binary image on the FPGA is compatible with the host program.

Additional information.text: Requested size 16384 bytes, implemented size 98304 bytes, stall-free, 6 reads and 2 writes.

For each replicate, 2 private copies were created to efficiently support multiple simultaneous workgroups. This resulted in 2.29 times increase in actual block RAM usage. Reducing the number of barriers or increasing max_work_group_size may help reduce this factor.
For each bank, 3 replicates were created to efficiently support multiple accesses. To reduce this factor, reduce number of read and write accesses.
